data: Mr. Brendan McCullian Mr. Brendan McCullian Mr. Brendan McCullian Graduate Student mccullian.1@osu.edu Physics Research Building, 180 191 West Woodruff Avenue Columbus, Ohio 43210 Google Map Brendan earned his B.S. in Physics from Penn State in 2014. He is currently a pre-candidacy graduate assistant at the Ohio State University and joined Professor P. Chris Hammel’s research group in 2015. He is studying magnetic bulk and thin film properties using cantilever magnetometry. He is also working on developing a scanning NV-diamond microscope for optically detected magnetic resonance experiments.
